# performDefaultImplementation()

**Instance Method**

Overridden by subclasses to provide a default implementation for the command represented by the receiver.

## Declaration

```swift
func performDefaultImplementation() -> Any?
```

## Discussion

Do not invoke this method directly. [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSScriptCommand/execute()] invokes this method when the command being executed is not supported by the class of the objects receiving the command. The default implementation returns `nil`.

You need to create a subclass of `NSScriptCommand` only if you need to provide a default implementation of a command.

## Executing the command

- **execute()**: Executes the command if it is valid and returns the result, if any.
